Finley Lamb suffers from rare brain abnormality Periventricular Nodular Heterotopia  . 
  It means many of his 'grey matter' cells have not migrated to the correct position . 
  He was born with a 90 per cent chance of developing Epilepsy and was unable to walk and talk . 
  But he took his first steps last year and now walks two miles to school . 
  Finley was diagnosed with the disorder when he was two years old . 
 